es and the Four Seasons as early 1960s rivals; the Mamas and the Papas and Crosby, Stills and Nash as later 1960s rivals; and the Beatles and the Temptations as decade-spanning counterparts. This is the first book to take an honest look at the themes running through the Beach Boys’ art and career as a whole and to examine where they sit inside our culture and politics—and why they still grab our attention.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 27. Okt 2021) 0aBeach Boys. 0aRock groupszUnited States. 0aRock musicxHistory and criticism. 0aRock musicianszUnited StatesvBiography. 0aRock musicians-United States-Biography. 0aSurf musiczUnited States. 7aMUSIC / Genres & Styles / Rock.2bisacsh40uhttps://doi.org/10.7560/31872040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781477318768423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781477318768/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_MUAR  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_MUAR  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK